text: The District Planning Committee is the only Constitutionally mandated planning body in India ( not even the Plng . Cmsn . /Niti Aayog or the State Planning Boards ) . As it is the state of integrated planning in the country has been a non starter despite of all the efforts taken during the UPA regime . However bodies like NITI Aayog , State Planning Commissions are still provided with resources and manpower so that they are able to take crucial decisions but when the question comes of empowering the DPC and enthusing the DPC members to perform as per the Act , theapathy of the Government is clearly visible with utter confusion , lack of any credible information and parallel orders . The most critical level of planning where there is a possibility of merging the rural and urban sector plans and ensuring the rural-urban continuum , ensuring convergence of schemes and programmes of the line departments and avoiding duplication , prioritising local level needs - is being neglected and subverted by adhoc and politically motivated actions . Its high time to walk the talk and allow DPCs to function with autonomy and necessary resources for effective integrated district planning , implementation and monitoring

Connecting Rucheng and Chenzhou , the bridge is renowned for its three back-to-back cable-stayed spans of 380 meters . Its pillars , all of which climb more than 100 meters high , are also groundbreaking . One of the four pillars rises 182 meters above the valley below , and is said to be the highest used in any cable-stayed bridge in the world .
